data.value: Sharm El Sheikh is located in between the Gulf of Aqaba, the Gulf of Suez, and the open body of the Red Sea. As a consequence, at the tip of the Sinai Peninsula those three different waters meet, resulting in a rich environment and feeding currents suitable for the optimal growth of corals and marine life.
